The London Stock Exchange has noimmediate comment on the U.S. Insider trading charge against asenior London executive of Merrill Lynch and Co, an Exchangespokesman said.    "This is a civil action in New York and no-one here has anyproper details yet," he added.    The London Exchange, which keeps in touch through the U.K.Government's information channels to the U.S. Securities andExchange Commission, will await further developments, he said.    Trade and Industry Department officials also declinedimmediate comment.    Merrill Lynch in London said any further amplification onthe SEC charge against its executive Nahum Vaskevitch wouldhave to come from the firms's New York office. Reuter&#3;